s UI can render the FR-6 attention strip\n926\t    without recomputing.\n927\t- **Boundedness** — every per-user query is parameterized by\n928\t  `recentLimit` (default 25) or `tokenLimit` (default 10). The user-detail\n929\t  page is a high-attention single-row admin surface; the limits keep it\n930\t  responsive even for power users with hundreds of game entries / claims.\n931\t  The function accepts `options.sql`/`options.recentLimit`/`options.tokenLimit`\n932\t  injection seams so the next iteration's tests can drive the parallel\n933\t  queries deterministically (matching iteration-12 / iteration-18 patterns).\n934\t- **No frontend wiring this iteration**. The existing `UserDetailCard` reads\n935\t  only `user`, `inboundReferral`, `outboundReferees`, and `telegram` — the new\n936\t  fields are populated but ignored by the current component. The next FR-6\n937\t  checklist item rewires `/users/[userId]` into the tabs/anchored sections\n938\t  layout per the spec; the iteration after that adds the dedicated query +\n939\t  component test coverage.\n940\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n941\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (173/173, no regressions; the existing\n942\t  `telegram-linked-queries.test.ts` still passes because `queries[0]` is the\n943\t  preserved linked_accounts join — the new `telegram_link_tokens` query runs\n944\t  as a separate parallel query well after `queries[0]`).\n945\t\n946\t## Iteration 19 — 2026-04-25 — OK\n947\t- **Log**: iteration-019.log\n948\t\n949\t## Iteration 19 — 2026-04-25T11:55:06Z — OK\n950\t- **Log**: iteration-019.log\n951\t\n952\t\n953\t## Iteration 20 — 2026-04-25\n954\t\n955\t- Replaced the 303-era `UserDetailCard` with a new\n956\t  `peek/src/components/user-detail-view.tsx` that renders the FR-6\n957\t  expanded user profile through the iteration-9 `DetailPanel`. Sections\n958\t  (in spec order) are `identity`, `linked-accounts`, `referrals`,\n959\t  `games`, `rewards`, `challenges`, `transactions`, `attention`. The\n960\t  panel renders both the anchor nav (jump-to) and the section bodies, so\n961\t  it covers the spec's \"tabs/anchored sections\" requirement without\n962\t  introducing client-side state.\n963\t- Above the panel:\n964\t  - `UserHeader` shows the heading (username → user_id fallback), wallet\n965\t    in monospace, and a small `<dl>` with `user_id` + joined date so the\n966\t    most-used identifiers stay visible no matter which section is\n967\t    scrolled to.\n968\t  - `AttentionStrip` renders a tone-coded `StatusChip` for every active\n969\t    attention flag (failed claim, dead queue event, active fraud flag,\n970\t    pending SOL crate payout, suspicious referral self/loop) so\n971\t    operators see the FR-6 attention signals before any section scroll.\n972\t    Hidden entirely when no flags are set, so clean users do not show a\n973\t    misleading warning band.\n974\t- Per-section rendering reuses the iteration-8/9 primitives (no new\n975\t  component contracts):\n976\t  - `Identity` — `<dl>` of profile fields (user_id, username, wallet,\n977\t    joined, avatar_url, heat_multiplier, profile_points_balance), with a\n978\t    shared `EmptyState` if every value is null.\n979\t  - `Linked accounts` — telegram link state `<dl>` + a sortless table of\n980\t    every `linked_accounts` row + a recent-tokens table from\n981\t    `telegram_link_tokens`. `StatusChip` tones reflect provider status\n982\t    (active=positive, revoked=negative) and token redemption state.\n983\t  - `Referrals` — inbound referrer card + referral-code metadata + KOL\n984\t    rate block (or empty state) + earnings/rebate summary + recent\n985\t    claims (status-chipped: paid=positive, failed/error=negative,\n986\t    processing=info) + outbound referees (each linkified to their own\n987\t    `/users/[userId]`).\n988\t  - `Games` — recent `game_entries` rows; match_id is a Link to\n989\t    `/games/${game}/rounds/${roundPda}` for the upcoming round-detail\n990\t    pages; `i