{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01W7XMaoCiEeN7L5BJoCF5Ni","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Checklist Audit\n\n26 items checked, 50 still `[ ]`. Many implementation iterations remain (frontend pages for `/growth/referrals`, `/growth/kol`, games/economy/queue/audit, mutation framework, exports, docs + verify). Cannot output DONE.\n\n## Iteration 27 Summary\n\nCompleted the FR-7 engine query module for the upcoming `/growth/referrals` and `/growth/kol` pages:\n\n- **`peek/src/server/db/queries/get-growth-referrals.ts`** — five exported entry points, all bounded server-side and using only existing tables:\n  - `getGrowthReferralOverview()` — eight FR-4 metrics (referrers, referred users, activated referred users, referrer earnings, referee rebates, pending claims, failed claims, KOL count) with stable ids, definitions, source tables, and drill-down hrefs.\n  - `listTopReferrers({ limit })` — per-referrer aggregate joining `referral_links`, `player_profiles`, `referral_codes`, `referral_earnings`, and pending `referral_claims`. Uses `LEFT JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT user_id FROM game_entries)` to avoid Cartesian explosion when computing active-referee count. Defaults to 50, capped at 250.\n  - `listKolPerformance({ limit })` — `referral_kol_rates` with linked performance from `referral_links` + `referral_earnings` aggregates. Defaults to 100, capped at 500.\n  - `listReferralClaims({ filters, limit })` — eight optional filters (status, userId, min/max amount, requestedFrom/To, txSignature, errorContains). Defaults to 100, capped at 500. The `status='failed'` value widens to `('failed','error')` so the command-center drill-down link works without a separate alias.\n  - `getReferralGraphNode(userId, { refereeLimit })` — one-hop graph node centered on a user (inbound referrer back-link + outbound referees forward-link).\n- **View models in `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`** — added `PeekGrowthOverviewMetricId`